<br>
The setting, KC, LCY.<br>
<br>
Im not getting much xp.<br>
no me either.<br>
dood.<br>
What ?<br>
This sux.<br>
Yeah, but what else is there to do ?<br>
Then Elendil chimed in.... I hear Vox is up.<br>
<br>
Was he serious ?<br>
Do people simply do that ? Do they just do pickup raids and go kill Vox ?<br>
<br>
Well, the answer i found out is yes.<br>
Apparently there was supposed to be an open raid on her that day, but it never happened.<br>
Somehow i got roped into leading this godforsaken dragon hunt.  With my group from KC, Elendil, Ntro, Urgreth, Nefertiari, Iziadiar (sp?).  A pally, warrior, chanter, cleric, necro, and myself, a druid.  Off we go to permafrost.  <br>
<br>
Sure enough, shes up.<br>
Now what ?<br>
<br>
So elendil starts shooting out tells to people on his friends list and they shoot out tells from there. a few hours later, and many many many many ports later we have about 5 groups ready to roll against the ice queen.  By this time its almost midnight PST.  People want to log and go to sleep.  Its 3am EST at this point.<br>
<br>
We begin the arduas buffing process, screwed up totally because this was my first raid i ever led, and only my second time at Vox.  Camp to chat, go over loot and groups and tactics and log back in.<br>
<br>
We rush in, wham, pin her against the wall.  people start dying trying to get her away from the wall.  Shes wiping out noble players left and right.... this is bad, real bad.... very very bad..... then WHAM with a final swipe of his mighty blade, Dalidinar a mighty dwarven paladin fell the great wurm.<br>
<br>
The loot was good, I myself won a tobrins Eyepatch as did Mystala.  A RBB was won by Negator.  A 100% wt reduction bag was won by Dalidinar.  A clerical 2hb was won by Qaladin, as rolled for by his friend Maakar.  (Qaladin was ld and couldn't log back on)  And probably best of all Rohinn of Veil of Shadows won a roll on a white dragon scale by about 30 points.<br>
<br>
I had a great time leading this raid, and it was truly a great learning experience for me.  That lesson of course being not to lead anymore raids. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    I receved dozens of tells from people thanking me for a great time even those that didn't win any loot.<br>
<br>
But most of all, i would like to thank EVERYONE who showed up.  I had one of the best times playing EQ tonight that i have ever had.  Frustrating, but fun.  I wish i could name you all, but i just don't remember everyone.<br>
Thanks again to everyone involved, i made a lot of new friends tonight !<br>
<br>
--EDIT--<br>
Oh, and it was amazing that a pickup raid like this, EVERYONE actually listened.  No one got us killed or anything by not listening !  There was one time when someone, we don't know who, trained about 7 IGs on the camp, but we took them out with only 2 deaths, and by that time Mystala and her watersprinkler were there. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR>
